<item>
            <title>[PIG-5159] Fix Pig not saving grunt history</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-5159</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After quitting Pig (grunt) and restarting it I cannot see my last Pig latin statements.&lt;br/&gt;
Cause is that pig history file (~/.pig_history) is only being read on Pig startup, but is not being written. This can be traced back to the recent jline upgrade &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3851&quot; title=&quot;Upgrade jline to 2.11&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3851&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3851&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13047010">PIG-5159</key>
            <summary>Fix Pig not saving grunt history</summary>
