                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15888350" author="szita" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2017 16:17:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like the old version of jline took care of history persistence itself (after each line being read from console): &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jline/jline/blob/master/src/main/java/jline/History.java#L102&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jline/jline/blob/master/src/main/java/jline/History.java#L102&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The new version doesn&apos;t, we have to call flush() explicitly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;daijy&lt;/a&gt;, can you please take a look at &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12855169/12855169_PIG-5159.0.patch&quot; title=&quot;PIG-5159.0.patch attached to PIG-5159&quot;&gt;PIG-5159.0.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15891183" author="rohini" created="Wed, 1 Mar 2017 22:21:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Thanks Adam for catching this issue and fixing it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15894577" author="szita" created="Fri, 3 Mar 2017 15:40:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for committing, Rohini&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
